{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"Gp/b4dqQaiUlfxUBdpqeqCrVlEc=","kind":"plan","title":"What's-new view Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"RcspbKbSv5BQIFPK6P3qLfh74Hw=","body":"# What's-new view Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Show what changed since the last sync, in both directions — `kref list --new` (incoming from teammates + your unpushed local changes) and `kref log --since-pull \u003cid\u003e` (your edits after the last pull).\n\n**Architecture:** `Store.Pull` is rewritten to drive `dag.MergeAll` directly (the same Fetch+merge `dag.Pull` does) and capture the entity ids it reports `New`/`Updated`, recorded — with each entry's post-pull op-count — into the per-tier git-config key `kref.incoming.\u003ctier\u003e` (rewritten each pull). `kref list --new`'s **incoming** half reads that; its **unpushed** half reuses 6a's `pushDelta` (tip ≠ `kref-pushed`). `kref log --since-pull \u003cid\u003e` splits the entry's op log at its recorded pull op-count. New flags on the existing `list`/`log` commands; logic in the store core. Reference: `docs/dev/specs/2026-06-20-unified-entry-model-design.md` §5 (what's-new resolution).\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, git-bug entity/dag (`dag.Fetch`/`MergeAll`, `entity.MergeResult`/`MergeStatus*`), `repository.LocalConfig`, ginkgo/gomega, Taskfile.\n\n---\n\n## Conventions for every task\n\n- **TDD loop:** failing test → run-fail → implement → run-pass → `gofmt -w` → commit.\n- **Test runner:** prefix Go commands with `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto`. `internal/store` + `cmd/kref` suites need `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks`. `task test`/`task lint` are canonical.\n- **Ignore LSP \"GOTOOLCHAIN=local / No packages found / undefined\" diagnostics** — stale noise.\n- **Do NOT run `git stash`.** Stage files by name. Every commit ends with:\n  `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e`\n- Tests use the bare-hub remote pattern: `repository.InitBareGoGitRepo(dir, \"kref\")`.\n\n## File structure\n\n| File | Change | Responsibility |\n|------|--------|----------------|\n| `internal/store/sync.go` | modify | `Store.Pull` captures incoming; add `recordIncoming` + key/parse helpers |\n| `internal/store/whatsnew.go` | create | `Store.WhatsNew`, `Store.SincePull` |\n| `internal/store/whatsnew_test.go` | create | pull-capture, WhatsNew, SincePull tests |\n| `internal/render/whatsnew.go` | create | `render.WhatsNew` |\n| `internal/render/whatsnew_test.go` | create | render test |\n| `cmd/kref/commands.go` | modify | `--new` on `newListCmd`, `--since-pull` on `newLogCmd` |\n| `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` | modify | CLI tests |\n| `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` | modify | docs |\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: `Store.Pull` captures incoming\n\n**Files:** Modify `internal/store/sync.go`; create `internal/store/whatsnew_test.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests** — create `internal/store/whatsnew_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/repository\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"whats-new pull capture\", func() {\n\tbareHub := func() string {\n\t\tGinkgoHelper()\n\t\torigin := GinkgoT().TempDir()\n\t\t_, err := repository.InitBareGoGitRepo(origin, \"kref\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\treturn origin\n\t}\n\n\tIt(\"Pull records the entries it brought in as incoming\", func() {\n\t\torigin := bareHub()\n\t\ta, err := Init(gitRepo(), \"A\", \"a@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = a.Close() })\n\t\tb, err := Init(gitRepo(), \"B\", \"b@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = b.Close() })\n\t\tExpect(a.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"origin\", origin)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"origin\", origin)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tid, err := a.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"Hello\", \"from A\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(a.Push(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.Pull(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\t// B saw the entry arrive.\n\t\tgot, err := b.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(got.Title).To(Equal(\"Hello\"))\n\t\tinc := b.incomingIDs(entry.TierShared)\n\t\tExpect(inc).To(ContainElement(id.String()))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"Pull with no remote changes records empty incoming\", func() {\n\t\torigin := bareHub()\n\t\tb, err := Init(gitRepo(), \"B\", \"b@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = b.Close() })\n\t\tExpect(b.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"origin\", origin)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.Pull(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed()) // nothing on the hub\n\t\tExpect(b.incomingIDs(entry.TierShared)).To(BeEmpty())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n(`incomingIDs` is a small unexported test-visible accessor implemented in Step 3.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm FAIL** — `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/...` → FAIL (undefined: b.incomingIDs; Pull doesn't record).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** — in `internal/store/sync.go`:\n\n1. Extend the import block to add `\"strconv\"`, `\"strings\"`, and `\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"` (alongside the existing `errors`, `fmt`, `identity`, `dag`, `repository`, `entry`).\n\n2. Replace the last line of `Store.Pull` (`return dag.Pull(...)`) with the captured Fetch+MergeAll:\n\n```go\n\tif _, err := dag.Fetch(entry.Definition(t), s.repo, remote); err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\tvar incoming []entity.Id\n\tfor m := range dag.MergeAll(entry.Definition(t), entry.WrapForRead(), s.repo, resolvers(s.repo), remote, s.author) {\n\t\tif m.Err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn m.Err\n\t\t}\n\t\tif m.Status == entity.MergeStatusInvalid {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"merge failure: %s\", m.Reason)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif m.Status == entity.MergeStatusNew || m.Status == entity.MergeStatusUpdated {\n\t\t\tincoming = append(incoming, m.Id)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn s.recordIncoming(t, incoming)\n```\n\n3. Add the helpers (place near the remote config helpers):\n\n```go\nfunc incomingKey(t entry.Tier) string { return \"kref.incoming.\" + string(t) }\n\n// recordIncoming stores this pull's New/Updated entries with their post-pull\n// op-count as \"kref.incoming.\u003ctier\u003e = hex:count hex:count ...\", rewritten each pull.\nfunc (s *Store) recordIncoming(t entry.Tier, ids []entity.Id) error {\n\tparts := make([]string, 0, len(ids))\n\tfor _, id := range ids {\n\t\te, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"read incoming %s: %w\", id, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tparts = append(parts, id.String()+\":\"+strconv.Itoa(len(e.Operations())))\n\t}\n\treturn s.repo.LocalConfig().StoreString(incomingKey(t), strings.Join(parts, \" \"))\n}\n\n// incomingEntries parses the recorded incoming set for a tier into id→op-count.\nfunc (s *Store) incomingEntries(t entry.Tier) map[string]int {\n\traw, err := s.repo.LocalConfig().ReadString(incomingKey(t))\n\tif err != nil || strings.TrimSpace(raw) == \"\" {\n\t\treturn map[string]int{}\n\t}\n\tout := map[string]int{}\n\tfor _, p := range strings.Fields(raw) {\n\t\thex, cnt, ok := strings.Cut(p, \":\")\n\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tn, err := strconv.Atoi(cnt)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tout[hex] = n\n\t}\n\treturn out\n}\n\n// incomingIDs returns just the ids recorded as incoming for a tier.\nfunc (s *Store) incomingIDs(t entry.Tier) []string {\n\tm := s.incomingEntries(t)\n\tids := make([]string, 0, len(m))\n\tfor hex := range m {\n\t\tids = append(ids, hex)\n\t}\n\treturn ids\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm PASS.**\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/store/sync.go internal/store/whatsnew_test.go\ngit add internal/store/sync.go internal/store/whatsnew_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): Pull captures incoming entries via MergeAll\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: `Store.WhatsNew`\n\n**Files:** Create `internal/store/whatsnew.go`; modify `internal/store/whatsnew_test.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test** — append to `whatsnew_test.go` (new `Describe`):\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"WhatsNew\", func() {\n\tbareHub := func() string {\n\t\tGinkgoHelper()\n\t\torigin := GinkgoT().TempDir()\n\t\t_, err := repository.InitBareGoGitRepo(origin, \"kref\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\treturn origin\n\t}\n\n\tIt(\"reports incoming entries and unpushed local entries\", func() {\n\t\torigin := bareHub()\n\t\ta, err := Init(gitRepo(), \"A\", \"a@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = a.Close() })\n\t\tb, err := Init(gitRepo(), \"B\", \"b@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = b.Close() })\n\t\tExpect(a.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"origin\", origin)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"origin\", origin)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tincomingID, err := a.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"FromA\", \"x\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(a.Push(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.Pull(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\t// B has a local unpushed entry too.\n\t\tlocalID, err := b.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"LocalB\", \"y\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n\t\tincoming, unpushed, err := b.WhatsNew()\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tincIDs := idsOf(incoming)\n\t\tunpIDs := idsOf(unpushed)\n\t\tExpect(incIDs).To(ContainElement(incomingID.String()))\n\t\tExpect(unpIDs).To(ContainElement(localID.String()))\n\t})\n})\n\nfunc idsOf(snaps []*entry.Snapshot) []string {\n\tout := make([]string, 0, len(snaps))\n\tfor _, s := range snaps {\n\t\tout = append(out, s.ID.String())\n\t}\n\treturn out\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm FAIL** — undefined b.WhatsNew.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** — create `internal/store/whatsnew.go`:\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\n// WhatsNew returns the entries that arrived in the last pull (incoming) and the\n// entries changed since the last push (unpushed), across syncable tiers.\nfunc (s *Store) WhatsNew() (incoming, unpushed []*entry.Snapshot, err error) {\n\ttiers, err := s.SyncableTiers()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t}\n\tincoming = []*entry.Snapshot{}\n\tunpushed = []*entry.Snapshot{}\n\tfor _, t := range tiers {\n\t\tfor hex := range s.incomingEntries(t) {\n\t\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(entityID(hex))\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue // entry may have been purged since the pull\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tincoming = append(incoming, snap)\n\t\t}\n\t\tdelta, err := s.pushDelta(t)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tfor _, id := range delta {\n\t\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tunpushed = append(unpushed, snap)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn incoming, unpushed, nil\n}\n```\n\nAdd a tiny helper in `whatsnew.go` (or reuse if one exists) to convert a hex string to `entity.Id`:\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n\nfunc entityID(hex string) entity.Id { return entity.Id(hex) }\n```\n\n(Combine the two imports into one block.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm PASS.**\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/store/whatsnew.go internal/store/whatsnew_test.go\ngit add internal/store/whatsnew.go internal/store/whatsnew_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): WhatsNew reports incoming + unpushed entries\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: `Store.SincePull`\n\n**Files:** Modify `internal/store/whatsnew.go`, `internal/store/whatsnew_test.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test** — append to the `WhatsNew` describe in `whatsnew_test.go`:\n\n```go\n\tIt(\"SincePull returns only the ops added after the pull (and flags no-baseline)\", func() {\n\t\torigin := bareHub()\n\t\ta, err := Init(gitRepo(), \"A\", \"a@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = a.Close() })\n\t\tb, err := Init(gitRepo(), \"B\", \"b@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = b.Close() })\n\t\tExpect(a.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"origin\", origin)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"origin\", origin)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tid, err := a.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"Doc\", \"v1\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(a.Push(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.Pull(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\t// No local edits yet → nothing since the pull.\n\t\tops, baseline, err := b.SincePull(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(baseline).To(BeTrue())\n\t\tExpect(ops).To(BeEmpty())\n\n\t\t// A local edit appears as \"since pull\".\n\t\tExpect(b.Update(id, \"v2 local\", \"\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tops, baseline, err = b.SincePull(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(baseline).To(BeTrue())\n\t\tExpect(len(ops)).To(BeNumerically(\"\u003e=\", 1))\n\n\t\t// An entry never pulled has no baseline.\n\t\tlocalID, err := b.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"LocalOnly\", \"z\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\t_, baseline, err = b.SincePull(localID)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(baseline).To(BeFalse())\n\t})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm FAIL** — undefined b.SincePull.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** — append to `internal/store/whatsnew.go`:\n\n```go\n// SincePull returns the entry's operations added after the last pull (the ops\n// beyond the recorded post-pull op-count). The bool is false when the entry has\n// no pull baseline (it was not part of any recorded pull), in which case the\n// full log is returned.\nfunc (s *Store) SincePull(id entity.Id) ([]entry.LogEntry, bool, error) {\n\tlog, err := s.Log(id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, false, err\n\t}\n\ttiers, err := s.SyncableTiers()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, false, err\n\t}\n\tfor _, t := range tiers {\n\t\tif count, ok := s.incomingEntries(t)[id.String()]; ok {\n\t\t\tif count \u003e len(log) {\n\t\t\t\tcount = len(log)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn log[count:], true, nil\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn log, false, nil\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm PASS.**\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/store/whatsnew.go internal/store/whatsnew_test.go\ngit add internal/store/whatsnew.go internal/store/whatsnew_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): SincePull splits an entry's log at the last pull\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: CLI — `list --new` and `log --since-pull`\n\n**Files:** Create `internal/render/whatsnew.go`, `internal/render/whatsnew_test.go`; modify `cmd/kref/commands.go`, `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing render test** — create `internal/render/whatsnew_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage render_test\n\nimport (\n\t\"bytes\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/render\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"WhatsNew rendering\", func() {\n\tIt(\"prints incoming and unpushed sections\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.WhatsNew(\u0026b,\n\t\t\t[]*entry.Snapshot{{ID: entity.Id(\"aaa1\"), Tier: \"shared\", Kind: \"spec\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"FromTeam\"}},\n\t\t\t[]*entry.Snapshot{{ID: entity.Id(\"bbb2\"), Tier: \"shared\", Kind: \"spec\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"MyLocal\"}},\n\t\t\tfalse)\n\t\tout := b.String()\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"Incoming\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"FromTeam\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring